text: Biryuchya Kosa () is a rural locality (a selo) and the administrative center of Biryuchekosinsky Selsoviet, Limansky District, Astrakhan Oblast, Russia. The population was 945 as of 2010. There are 8 streets. == Geography == It is located 130 km from Astrakhan, 40 km from Liman. == References == Category:Rural localities in Limansky District
title: Biryuchya Kosa
